HEADWORD: Rushbuckler
<hw>Rush"buc`kler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bullying and
violent person; a braggart; a swashbuckler.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That flock of stout, bragging <qex>rushbucklers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Robynson (More's Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rushed</ent>⟦br⟧
